Here's an example of using an array of integers as parameters for a procedure:
```
procedure add_numbers(x, y) is
    local sum = 0;
    for i = 1 to 10 do
        sum = sum + x[i] + y[i];
    end for;
    display('The sum of the numbers is:', sum);
end procedure;
```
This code demonstrates how to use an array of integers as parameters for a procedure. It initializes the sum variable to zero and then adds up all the elements in the array. Finally, it displays the final sum value on screen.

